EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education

EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring the police department to submit to the council reports of crime in all parks and playgrounds within the City that are greater than one acre in size.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the police department to submit to the council reports of crime in all parks and playgrounds within the City that are greater than one acre in size.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the New York State Legislature to enact S3644/A2012, and for the Governor to sign the legislation into law. The legislation gives authority to the New York Police Department to enforce Vehicle and Traffic Law Section 1146, even if the police officer was not present at the time of the crash, as long as the officer has reasonable cause to believe the violation was committed by the driver.
EventItemMatterName: NYPD to enforce Vehicle and Traffic Law Section 1146, regardless of whether the police officer witnessed the incident. (S.3644/A.2012)
